title: How the Aces beat the Liberty to keep their season alive
description: Las Vegas shut down Sabrina Ionescu to beat New York for the first time this year and stave off elimination in the WNBA semifinals.

title: Aces end 5-game slide to Liberty to avoid sweep in Game 3
description: The Aces got their first win against the Liberty this season and staved off elimination, thanks in large part to their defense holding Sabrina Ionescu to four points.

title: Napheesa Collier, Lynx win Game 3 over Sun in WNBA playoffs
description: Napheesa Collier scored 26 points as the Lynx beat the Sun 90-81 to take a 2-1 lead in the best-of-five semifinal series. Game 4 is Sunday, when a win for Minnesota would put it back in the WNBA Finals for the first time since 2017.

title: Tiffany Hayes latest from Aces to win Sixth Player of the Year
description: Aces guard Tiffany Hayes was named the WNBA Sixth Player of the Year, marking the fifth time in the past six seasons that a Las Vegas player has won the award.
